result.execSummary:
The defendant Enrique H Gonzalez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Supplier Violation of Food Stamp Benefits (>$100-$5000) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.92(2)(e).
  • Attempt Unauthorized Use of Food Stamps (>$100-$5000) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.92(2)(f).
  • Attempt Knowingly Traffic Food Stamps (>$100-$5000) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.92(2)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the State, Defense counsel and defendant.
Defense counsel advises Court that defendant will stipulate to the restitution requested.

-  Court sets Restitution at $3,325.92  (Restitution to be sent to:  Dept of Health Services, Attn: Crystal Baker, 1 West Wilson Street, P.O. Box 309, Madison, WI  53703)

As to Count 1:
Court sentenced defendant to serve  6   months  in the House of Correction with Huber privileges for employment, credit for 1 (one) day served.  Good time credit may be earned. 

As to Count 2:
Court sentenced defendant to serve  6  months  in the House of Correction, consecutive to the sentence imposed as to Count 1; with Huber privileges for employment.  Good time credit may be earned.

As to Count 3:
Court sentenced defendant to serve  6  months  in the House of Correction, concurrent to the sentence imposed as to Counts 1 and 2; with Huber privileges for employment.  Good time credit may be earned.

As to all counts:
Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for  18  MONTHS with the following conditions:
-  Probation is concurrent
-  Follow all rules of probation
-  AODA assessment and any treatment
-  Absolute sobriety
-  No illegal substances
-  Random urine screens
-  Seek/Maintain employment
-  Pay Restitution in the amount ordered during the term of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
-  Per Wisconsin State Stat. 946.92(3)(e) - suspension from the food stamp program
-  Perform 60 hours of community service
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis and pay the surcharge (if not already done so) during the term of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
